{"type":"message","id":"01ac15b1","parentId":"930c5136","timestamp":"2026-03-08T09:35:37.278Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"收到，本王这就去扫一眼技能列表！"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2uojuvtzlubfmdghpxqomif5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"volcengine-plan","model":"ark-code-latest","usage":{"input":39096,"output":53,"cacheRead":3384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42533,"cost":{"input":0.0000039096,"output":1.06e-8,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0000039202}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772962527038}}
{"type":"message","id":"1933b2be","parentId":"01ac15b1","timestamp":"2026-03-08T09:35:37.303Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2uojuvtzlubfmdghpxqomif5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772962537299}}
